#: ../../../release_details/9.5/add-state_metadata_vtk_fields-vtkConduitSource.md:1
msgid "vtkConduitSource: Add state/metadata/vtk_fields node"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.5/add-state_metadata_vtk_fields-vtkConduitSource.md:3
msgid ""
"When defining fields in a Conduit tree, it is often useful to include "
"metadata about the fields that can be interpreted by VTK, and utilized "
"appropriately. To that end, we have added a new node to the Conduit tree "
"that can be used to store metadata about the fields in the tree. This node "
"is called `state/metadata/vtk_fields`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.5/add-state_metadata_vtk_fields-vtkConduitSource.md:7
msgid ""
"Each child of the `state/metadata/vtk_fields` node has a name that "
"corresponds to a field in the tree. The number of children of the `state/"
"metadata/vtk_fields` node should not match the number of `fields` in the "
"tree since not every field needs to have metadata."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.5/add-state_metadata_vtk_fields-vtkConduitSource.md:11
msgid "The current metadata that can be stored for each field is:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.5/add-state_metadata_vtk_fields-vtkConduitSource.md:13
msgid ""
"`attribute_type`: It is a string and represents the attribute type of a "
"field that, so that VTk can use an attribute array, such as `GlobalIds`. The "
"values uses are the entries of `vtkDataSetAttributes::AttributeTypes` + "
"`Ghosts`. The complete list of values is:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.5/add-state_metadata_vtk_fields-vtkConduitSource.md:16
msgid "`Scalars`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.5/add-state_metadata_vtk_fields-vtkConduitSource.md:17
msgid "`Vectors`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.5/add-state_metadata_vtk_fields-vtkConduitSource.md:18
msgid "`Normals`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.5/add-state_metadata_vtk_fields-vtkConduitSource.md:19
msgid "`TCoords`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.5/add-state_metadata_vtk_fields-vtkConduitSource.md:20
msgid "`Tensors`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.5/add-state_metadata_vtk_fields-vtkConduitSource.md:21
msgid "`GlobalIds`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.5/add-state_metadata_vtk_fields-vtkConduitSource.md:22
msgid "`PedigreeIds`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.5/add-state_metadata_vtk_fields-vtkConduitSource.md:23
msgid "`EdgeFlag`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.5/add-state_metadata_vtk_fields-vtkConduitSource.md:24
msgid "`Tangents`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.5/add-state_metadata_vtk_fields-vtkConduitSource.md:25
msgid "`RationalWeights`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.5/add-state_metadata_vtk_fields-vtkConduitSource.md:26
msgid "`HigherOrderDegrees`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.5/add-state_metadata_vtk_fields-vtkConduitSource.md:27
msgid "`ProcessIds`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.5/add-state_metadata_vtk_fields-vtkConduitSource.md:28
msgid "`Ghosts`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.5/add-state_metadata_vtk_fields-vtkConduitSource.md:29
msgid ""
"`values_to_replace` and `replacement_values`: These two are vectors of "
"values that be used to replace specific values in the field. This is useful "
"when the field has some values that are not valid for VTK. For example, the "
"`vtkGhostType` array uses specific values that other ghost cell generator "
"algorithms may not use. In this case, the `values_to_replace` would be the "
"values that need to be replaced, and the `replacement_values` would be the "
"values that should replace them. The two vectors should have the same length."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.5/add-state_metadata_vtk_fields-vtkConduitSource.md:35
msgid "Example:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.5/add-state_metadata_vtk_fields-vtkConduitSource.md:37
msgid ""
"conduit_cpp::Node mesh;\n"
"CreateUniformMesh(3, 3, 3, mesh);\n"
"\n"
"std::vector<int> cellGhosts(8, 0);\n"
"cellGhosts[2] = 1;\n"
"\n"
"conduit_cpp::Node resCellFields = mesh[\"fields/other_ghosts\"];\n"
"resCellFields[\"association\"] = \"element\";\n"
"resCellFields[\"topology\"] = \"mesh\";\n"
"resCellFields[\"volume_dependent\"] = \"false\";\n"
"resCellFields[\"values\"] = cellGhosts;\n"
"\n"
"std::vector<int> cellGhostValuesToReplace(1, 1);\n"
"std::vector<int> cellGhostReplacementValues(1, vtkDataSetAttributes::"
"HIDDENCELL);\n"
"\n"
"std::vector<int> cellGhostsMetaData(1, 1);\n"
"conduit_cpp::Node ghostMetaData = mesh[\"state/metadata/vtk_fields/"
"other_ghosts\"];\n"
"ghostMetaData[\"attribute_type\"] = \"Ghosts\";\n"
"ghostMetaData[\"values_to_replace\"] = cellGhostValuesToReplace;\n"
"ghostMetaData[\"replacement_values\"] = cellGhostReplacementValues;\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.5/add-state_metadata_vtk_fields-vtkConduitSource.md:60
msgid ""
"Lastly, the usage of `ascent_ghosts` has been deprecated and should be "
"replaced with the new `state/metadata/vtk_fields` node, as shown above."
msgstr ""
